    - "itertools.compress.__name__ == 'compress' (len=8); compress is a C-level type that filters elements from data returning only those that have a corresponding element in selectors that evaluates to True; verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.compress.__module__ == 'itertools' (len=9); compress is defined in the itertools C extension module; verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.compress.__qualname__ == 'compress' (len=8); compress is a top-level C type so qualname equals name; verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.compress.__doc__.__class__.__name__ == 'str' (len=3); compress has a docstring that is a Python str instance; verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

